  "prompt": "If you open a microwave oven before the beep will it release deadly microwave radiation?",
  "response": "No, opening a microwave oven before it beeps will not release deadly microwave radiation. Microwave ovens are designed with safety features that prevent them from operating when the door is open. The microwave radiation is contained within the oven, and the device automatically stops generating microwaves as soon as the door is opened, regardless of whether the timer has ended or not. Therefore, it is safe to open the door at any time while the microwave is running, as it will not emit harmful radiation. However, doing so may expose you to heat or steam from the food being cooked, so caution should still be exercised.",
